      "lesson title": "Using AI with Loyalty Program Data",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces beginners to the practical and ethical considerations of using artificial intelligence alongside loyalty programme data. You will explore how AI can analyse customer behaviour and purchasing patterns to generate personalised offers and targeted communications. However, the lesson also highlights the significant risks involved, including unintended profiling, data bias, and the potential to treat customers unfairly or unlawfully. By the end of the lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to use AI responsibly when working with sensitive loyalty data, and how to recognise when its outputs may cause harm. The aim is to give you a solid, grounded foundation so you can approach AI tools with both confidence and caution.",
